<p>GDP growth: 0.3% GDP: $1,537bn (PPP: $1,489) Inflation: 1.8% Population: 46.3m GDP per head: $33,180 (PPP: $32,140)</p>

<p>The centre-right People's Party (PP) was poised to retake power from the Spanish Socialist Workers' Party in early elections scheduled for November 2011. But as with all recent Spanish governments, the dominant party will need the support of regional groups to hold power, giving much influence to Catalans and Basques. A PP government will toe the austere line imposed by Spain's precarious fiscal and financial position, and add a reform programme designed to encourage private investment. The economy, on the long climb back from recession, will grow fractionally.</p>

